name: TB-303 Mounted Canvas
description: The TB-303 was originally intended to be an accompaniment for solo guitarists in the early 80s, but didn't fulfil its true potential until some time after it was released. As well as being used in electro tracks, it unintentionally spawned a sound that was synonymous with a whole musical genre in the late 80s – Acid House. Available in 4 colours and 3 sizes, prices starting from £126. Click below for colour/size options. Please contact us if you require a quote for a bespoke colour and/or size. PLEASE NOTE: Mounted canvas prints are available in the UK only and are made to order, so please be aware of production times when ordering. All sizes are in millimetres (width x height). name: 44-16 T-shirt
description: This Electric Sun T-shirt looks back to the iconic number plate designs from the beginning of the eighties as BMX was taking off on a massive scale, and uses the original numbering sported by many racers of the day. This Tee is dedicated to the legendary riders of that era, such as Bob Haro, R.L. Osbourne, Harry Leary, and Eddie Fiola (to name but a few), who paved the way for the future of BMX and inspired kids globally. Electric Sun salute you! Riders ready… Pedals ready… GO! This heavyweight T-shirt (205 gsm) is made from 100% pre-shrunk cotton and has a soft, quality feel. It is light blue and has 4 screen-printed colours (white, red, blue and black) on the front. This design has had an initial print run of only 30 Tees, each one individually numbered and available exclusively online. To calculate the cost in your currency, click here.

name: GAMEBOY Mounted Canvas
description: Released in 1989, the Gameboy single-handedly revolutionised portable gaming. Despite being basic (by today's standards), it sold millions and still remains a popular icon of gaming history. The best selling game was Tetris… remarkably simple, but highly addictive. name: I LOVE ACID T-Shirt
description: Cast your mind back, if you can, to 1988 and the (second) ‘Summer of Love’. The headline-grabbing acid-house phenomenon was everywhere. This T-shirt is dedicated to the machine that made it all possible over 20 years ago – the Roland TB-303… This heavyweight T-shirt (185 gsm) is made from 100% pre-shrunk ring-spun cotton and has a soft, quality feel. It is crisp white and has two screen-printed colours (black & red) on the front and one colour (black) on the back. This design will have an initial print run of only 50 Tees, each one individually numbered and available exclusively online. To calculate the cost in your currency, click here.
